definition: to admire/to hold in high esteem
to respect/to admire/to venerate/by the emperor himself

sentences.english: Some people go to great lengths to make their homes attractive.
sentences.chinese: 有些人千方百計使他們的家令人欽羨。

sentences.english: At twenty-one he took his degree-a respectable degree, but not a very high one.
sentences.chinese: 二十一歲他獲得了一個不很高，但也令人欽羨的學位。
